A transaction intended to update Colleague with externally modified data can in , turn trigger Colleague to generate a transaction to update external , applications. To mitigate this 'mirror-image' effect, the AMQP message broker , maintains an internal record of each transaction inbound to Colleague as a , means of identifying (and suppressing) a resulting 'mirror-image' outbound , transaction. The value stored in this field identifies the useful lifespan that , the broker assigns to the internal record.

We need to provide a back door method to disable, the GUI graph on an account wide basis.  If this parameter is set on, UIPR to 'Y', the terminal-style bar graph will be used in the entire, account., It is also our intention to allow Clients to disable the graph on a, process by process case as well. Obsolete; only used with legacy retired wIntegrate UI products, ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~, October 25 2005  04:33pm  Paul Summers, Added to enable process running S.UI.FTP to adjust the absolute, path of the Unidata files to match the "view" of ftp.  In NT,, ftp can be set to any necessary level by the system administrator., This view may or may not be the same as the absolute path of a file, in a given account. This field allows the system administrator, to specify the prefix to remove from the absolute path in order to, arrive at the proper directory level for ftp to recognize., , For example, at Datatel we have a development account in directory, path D:\Datatel\apps\sdnt4db\...  However, ftp can only "see" as high, as "\apps\sdnt4db...  Therefore, this field must contain "D:\Datatel", in order for the ftp processing to know to remove that string from the, absolute path for data files before building the winteg ftp script. Thi, ensures that ftp and the script are looking at the same directory, level.

Default Input Processing: $UC, , *************** - to add a new service - *************************, *, * See the PURPOSE field of UT.VALCODES / GRAS.SERVICES, *, ******************************************************************, , * Get list of valid service codes, *, XL.ALLOWED.CODES = TRIM( '* PE PX AE AX AD HE HX CC GS NK FE DE NS KS CT' ), * Add numbers 1-9, CONVERT " " TO @FM IN XL.ALLOWED.CODES, FOR X = 1 TO 9; XL.ALLOWED.CODES<-1> = X; NEXT X, * Add letters A-Z, XA = SEQ("A"), XZ = SEQ("Z"), FOR X = XA TO XZ; XL.ALLOWED.CODES<-1> = CHAR(X); NEXT X, , , , * Copy entered data to working variable "XL.ENTRIES" as a, * fieldmark-delimited list of service codes., XL.ENTRIES = EDITED.DATA, * Allow comma or space (or both) to be the delimiter, CONVERT ',' TO ' ' IN XL.ENTRIES, XL.ENTRIES = TRIM( XL.ENTRIES ), CONVERT ' ' TO @FM IN XL.ENTRIES, , , * Break the entered list up into two lists,, *  XL.GOOD.CODES (valid entries with dups removed) and, *  XL.BAD.CODES (invalid entries), *, XL.BAD.CODES = "", XL.GOOD.CODES = "", X.NUM.ENTRIES = DCOUNT( XL.ENTRIES, @FM ), FOR X.SI = 1 TO X.NUM.ENTRIES,    * get next requested service code,    X.CODE = XL.ENTRIES< X.SI >, ,    * If this is a valid service code...,    LOCATE X.CODE IN XL.ALLOWED.CODES< 1 > SETTING X.NOTUSED THEN,       * If not yet on the good codes list, add it,       LOCATE X.CODE IN XL.GOOD.CODES<1> SETTING X.NOTUSED ELSE XL.GOOD.CODES< -1 > = X.CODE,    END ELSE,       XL.BAD.CODES< -1 > = X.CODE,    END, NEXT X.SI, , , , * Copy the list of valid codes back to EDITED.DATA, SWAP @FM WITH ' ' IN XL.GOOD.CODES, EDITED.DATA = XL.GOOD.CODES, , , , * If any bad codes were removed, let user know, X.NUM.BAD.CODES = DCOUNT( XL.BAD.CODES, @FM ), IF ( X.NUM.BAD.CODES GT 0 ) THEN,    BEGIN CASE,       CASE ( X.NUM.BAD.CODES EQ X.NUM.ENTRIES ),     * ALL the codes were bad -- Reprompt,     MSG = 'Invalid entry',     ERROR.OCCURRED = 1,  CASE ( X.NUM.BAD.CODES EQ 1 ),     MSG = 'Invalid code "':XL.BAD.CODES:'" removed',     WARNING.OCCURRED = 1,       CASE 1,     MSG = 'Invalid codes "': CONVERT(@FM,',',XL.BAD.CODES): '" removed',     WARNING.OCCURRED = 1,    END CASE, END

JP.HOLD.FILE.ID and JP.HOLD.PRINTER form a table which provides, a mapping of HOLD file IDs to the <appl>.PRINTERS records to, which they are associated., , The table was created 1/2/07 for ENV_SCR_10965.  It's used, by UTBROWSE. Toolcdd Lkup Pre Reso Hook: $UC, , EDITED.DATA = TRIM(EDITED.DATA), X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA = EDITED.DATA, , * Assume we'll need to perform a query to get our ID list unless otherwise specified, X.PERFORM.QUERY = 1, X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA = "", , BEGIN CASE,    CASE EDITED.DATA = "@",  * want the last permission.id; don't change value of edited.data,       X.PERFORM.QUERY = 0,       ,    CASE EDITED.DATA = "..." AND LEN(TRIM(EDITED.DATA)) = 3,       * they want to see all records available, no need to modify,  * what was entered,  X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA = EDITED.DATA,  ,    CASE LEN(A.PERMISSION.ID) AND (EDITED.DATA = A.PERMISSION.ID) AND THREAD.FLAG,       * this is a thread and they are passing ID, need to modify,       X.PERFORM.QUERY = 0,  ,    CASE 1,       * get our record IDs from the PERMISSION entity by looking up against the,       * PERMISSION.CODE field,       ,       * Set edited.data to '...' to force the lookup,       EDITED.DATA = '...',       ,  X.ELIPSIS.FOUND = 0,  X.SPACE.FOUND = 0,  X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA = "",       ,       X.ELIPSIS.FOUND = INDEX(X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA,"...",1),       IF (X.ELIPSIS.FOUND >= 1) THEN,     * already has elipses, don't add more,     X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA = X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA,       END ELSE,     X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA = "...": SQUOTE(X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA) :"...",  END, END CASE, , IF X.PERFORM.QUERY THEN,    * Need to perform a query to get the data for the search results,    X.STMT = 'SELECT PERMISSION',    X.STMT:= ' WITH @ID = "':X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA:'"',    X.STMT:= ' OR WITH PERMISSION.CODE LIKE ' : DQUOTE(X.LOOKUP.EDITED.DATA),    CALL S.EXECUTE(X.STMT),    XL.PERMISSION.IDS = '',    CALL S.READLIST(XL.PERMISSION.IDS, '', ''), ,    X.PERMISSION.COUNT = DCOUNT(XL.PERMISSION.IDS, @FM),    IF X.PERMISSION.COUNT = 0 THEN,       * None selected; change edited.data back to the originally entered value,       * so the user may use that one as a new ID if they wish,  EDITED.DATA = X.ORIG.EDITED.DATA,    END ELSE,  * Show search results otherwise, even if only a single match found; this is done,       * so that the user may select the 'Add' option to add a new record that may be,       * similar to those already out there,  SELECT.ID.LIST = CHANGE(XL.PERMISSION.IDS, @FM, @VM),    END, END
